The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Lillee to visit NCA today

New Delhi: Dennis Lillee will interact with Indias top pace bowlers at the National Cricket Academy in Bangalore Saturday in response to an invitation from new cricket coach Greg Chappell. 

Lillee, director of the MRF Pace Foundation in Chennai, will spend the entire day at the academy where the pacers are currently undergoing a physical conditioning camp. 

The MRF Pace Foundation has confirmed Lillees visit to Bangalore. He will be accompanied by T. A. Sekar, chief coach of the foundation. 

He will watch the bowlers at the nets Saturday and conduct a video analysis of their actions. He will also interact with Chappell on the future course of action. 

 (PTI) 




